const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/kettle-repair/brands/cleveland-range/";

const title = "Cleveland Range Kettle Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = `Cleveland Range steam jacketed kettle repair across SoCal. Tilt-Kettle series, KGL/KEL steam-jacketed, KDL direct-steam. Welbilt portfolio. $120 dx.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Who owns Cleveland Range?",
    a: "Cleveland Range is part of the Welbilt portfolio. Welbilt acquired Cleveland Range in 2008. Welbilt itself was acquired by Ali Group in 2022, so Cleveland Range's ultimate parent is Ali Group, with Welbilt as the immediate corporate parent. Sister brands within Welbilt: Garland (commercial cooking), Frymaster (fryers), Pitco (fryers), Manitowoc Ice (ice machines), Lincoln Foodservice (conveyor ovens), Convotherm (combi ovens), Delfield (commercial refrigeration), Wells (electric specialty fryers). At Ali Group level, Cleveland Range is also a sister brand to Beverage-Air, Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic, and Champion. The corporate structure matters for service: Welbilt's parts network is well-developed and OEM parts availability is strong across the Cleveland Range product family."
  },
  {
    q: "Which Cleveland Range kettle models do you service?",
    a: "Full Cleveland Range steam-jacketed and direct-steam kettle line. KGL gas-fired steam-jacketed (KGL-25, KGL-40, KGL-60, KGL-80, KGL-100 model sizes by gallon capacity). KEL electric steam-jacketed (KEL-25, KEL-40, KEL-60, KEL-80). KDL direct-steam (kettle uses building-supplied steam rather than self-generating). MKDL mixer-kettle combination units. Tilt-Kettle series (manual and motorized tilt for emptying). Plus the SE table-top steam kettle for smaller operations."
  },
  {
    q: "What fails most often on Cleveland Range kettles?",
    a: "On gas-fired KGL units the leading service items are: pilot won't stay lit (thermopile failure year 4-7, $260-440 all-in), gas valve failure (year 8-12, $480-720), pressure relief valve verification (annual safety inspection per California boiler code where applicable), steam jacket water level controls. On electric KEL units: heating element failure (year 6-10, $640-920), contactor relay (year 7-9, $340-540), pressure relief valve service. Across both: water-level sight glass cleaning, jacket water make-up (deionized water management), tilt mechanism service on Tilt-Kettle models."
  },
  {
    q: "Do steam jacketed kettles need a boiler permit in LA?",
    a: "Depends on the size and the configuration. California boiler safety regulations cover pressure vessels above certain thresholds; most Cleveland Range KGL/KEL kettles are below the unfired pressure vessel exemption threshold but require annual pressure-relief-valve inspection per CA Title 8 (occupational safety). Direct-steam KDL units that connect to a building boiler system are subject to whatever permit applies to the central boiler. We coordinate annual relief valve inspection documentation; we don't act as a regulatory authority. For boiler-permit-specific questions on a new install or a major retrofit, consult your facility's mechanical engineer or a boiler-licensed specialty contractor."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Cleveland Range kettle repair cost?",
    a: "$120 commercial diagnostic, applied to repair. Most Cleveland Range kettle repairs run $260-820 all-in. Thermopile replacement $260-440. Gas valve replacement $480-720. Heating element on electric KEL $640-920. Pressure relief valve replacement (annual or as needed) $280-440. Tilt mechanism service $340-540. Sight glass replacement $200-340. Steam jacket water-level control $340-540. Larger repairs (combination of multiple components on year 12+ unit) can run $1,200-2,000. We quote in writing before any parts are ordered."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Cleveland Range parts hard to source?",
    a: "No. Welbilt parts network has strong distribution across North America with 3-7 day standard ship on common service items (thermopiles, gas valves, heating elements, contactors, pressure relief valves). Common parts we stock on the van for the major KGL/KEL model sizes. Specialty parts (jacket assemblies, full mixer-kettle controllers, motorized tilt drives) are dealer-order with typical 5-10 day ship through Welbilt's authorized service network. We confirm part availability during the diagnostic."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. Cleveland Range component warranties (where applicable) are processed separately through Welbilt's authorized service network. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410, BBB A+ accredited."
  }
];

